@arcticlass of or relating to the country, country people or life, or agriculture.....

If it means bringing Inuit and Scots together, then I am for it.  That said, Inuit have more in common with Gaelic Scotland than they would with Edinburgh.

Thief by Michael Mann is fun for all the family, specifically if your family includes a metalworker and an engineering historian who are thrilled to a) see a thermite lance in action, and b) discuss thermite lances at length.
@connor_pimm @teesbirds1 @nybirdnews Not Bonxie or Pom. Juv Arctic or Long-tailed. Leaning towards the latter...

@IanDunt Always been fascinated by this story. Michael Palin's book 'Erebus' is very good. There's a Landseer based on the Franklin expedition called 'Man Proposes, God Disposes' at Royal Holloway College. It's considered unlucky and they cover it up when students do their exams.

@Nickgoatman last year I was very late getting my Arctic Tern tick (at Framton). It stayed in front of the sailing club. The commons down the other end were noisy, boisterous & aggressive around the rafts. To me it was obviously keeping out of their way.
While everyone was following Venta Maersk, the French Navy sailed from Norway to the Bering Strait in early September without #icebreaker escort: https://t.co/AiaY40IaLO (in French)
